@NODE "CopyFilterText" "CopyFilterText"
@TOC "MAIN"

Function         : CopyFilterText

Prototype        : void CopyFilterText( char *dest, char *source);

Purpose          : copies the source string to the given destination, removing MCI,
                   CR/LF and, converting each TAB to 3 spaces in the process.

                   this is the function used to prepare text to be displayed in
                   CNet GUIs

Arguments        : dest   - pointer to a string where the filtered text is placed.
                   source - string containing the text to copy and filter.
                   
Returns          : none

Known bugs       : none

See also         : 
@ENDNODE

@NODE "CountDirEntries" "CountDirEntries"
@TOC "MAIN"

Function         : CountDirEntries

Prototype        : LONG CountDirEntries(struct @{"CNetFileEntry" LINK "cnetinclude:files.h/main" 4} *list);

Purpose          : Count the number of entries on the current linked list of
                   CNetFileEntries (non-inclusive of parent and child entries)

Arguments        : the list to examine

Returns          : the number of file and directories in the list.
                   
Known bugs       : none

See also         : 
