@NODE "CreateDirEntry" "CreateDirEntry"
@TOC "MAIN"

Function         : CreateDirEntry

Prototype        : struct @{"CNetFileEntry" LINK "cnetinclude:files.h/main" 4} *CreateDirEntry(struct @{"FileInfoBlock" LINK "include:dos/dos.h/main" 60} *fib);

Purpose          : Allocate memory for a CNetFileEntry structure and return a
                   pointer to the allocated, initialized and filled
                   CNetFileEntry structure.

                   see the CNetFileEntry structure in include/files.h for a
                   description of the variables/fields within.

Arguments        : fib - a FileInfoBlock containing the information for the
                         entry to be created.

Returns          : pointer to the resultant CNetFileEntry structure.
                   NULL on failure
                   
Known bugs       : none

See also         : 
@ENDNODE

@NODE "CreateFolderName" "CreateFolderName"
@TOC "MAIN"

Function         : CreateFolderName

Prototype        : UBYTE CreateFolderName(char *destpath, char *UUCP, char *foldername);

Purpose          : Fill a string with the full path to a user's mail folder.

Arguments        : destpath   - the destination string to receive the user's mail
                                path.
                   @{"UUCP" LINK "cnetinclude:users.h/main" 154}       - the mail ID of a given user
                   foldername - the name of the desired folder .

Returns          : currently, always 0

Known bugs       : none
@ENDNODE

@NODE "CreateMailDir" "CreateMailDir"
@TOC "MAIN"

Function         : CreateMailDir

Prototype        : void CreateMailDir( char *uucpid);

Purpose          : Creates the physical disk path where a user's mail will
                   be filed.

Arguments        : uucpid - @{"UUCP" LINK "cnetinclude:users.h/main" 154}/mail ID of the user

Returns          : none

Known bugs       : none
@ENDNODE

@NODE "DelayAddItems" "DelayAddItems"
@TOC "MAIN"

Function         : DelayAddItems

Prototype        : void DelayAddItems( struct @{"SubboardType4" LINK "cnetinclude:subs.h/main" 439} *s );

Purpose          : Delay the saving of items to subboard data files

Arguments        : s - the subboard in which a delay is desired

Notes            : It is sometimes desirable (eg. when importing/posting many
                   items/messages) to delay the actual saving of those items
                   to CNet data files until all items for a particular subboard
                   are processed. This function accomplishes that task.

                   Make sure to call @{"FlushAddItems" LINK "FlushAddItems"} after all message/item
                   posting/importing is complete.

Returns          : none

Known bugs       : none

See also         : FlushAddItems
@ENDNODE

@NODE "DirectorySize" "DirectorySize"
@TOC "MAIN"

Function         : DirectorySize

Prototype        : ULONG DirectorySize( char *dir, BPTR lock );

Purpose          : Obtain the amount of space (in bytes) occupied by the files in a
                   directory (non-recursive)

Arguments        : dir  - optional name of directory to be examined
                   lock - optional lock pertaining to directory to be examined

Notes            : One of the arguments must be supplied.  If a lock is
                   specified, the dir arguent is ignored.

Returns          : size, in bytes, occupied by files in the directory

Known bugs       : 4 GB limitation on total size of directory.  Anything larger
                   will roll this value.
@ENDNODE

