@NODE "FindHandle" "FindHandle"
@TOC "MAIN"

Function         : FindHandle

Prototype        : long FindHandle( short *n, char *name, short id );

Purpose          : Find the account number of the user to which a
                   handle belongs.

Arguments        : n    = pointer to the variable to receive the account
                          to which the handle belongs
                   name = the handle being queried
                   id   = an optional account number for handle verification

Description      : If id is non-zero, this function will perform a
                   verification and return TRUE if the given handle
                   belongs to the given account (id)

                   if id is zero, this function will perform a search and,
                   if the handle was found, will fill n with the
                   accountnumber of the user to whom it belongs and
                   subsequently return TRUE.
                   

Returns          : TRUE if the handle was found/verified
                   FALSE if the handle was not found/verified

Known bugs       : none
@ENDNODE

@NODE "FindOrdinal" "FindOrdinal"
@TOC "MAIN"

Function         : FindOrdinal

