Arguments        : List - an Exec list pointer in which the desired node resides
                   N    -  the number of the desired node
                   
Returns          : Nth node in the Exec list

Known bugs       : none

See also         : 
@ENDNODE

@NODE "FindParent" "FindParent"
@TOC "MAIN"

Function         : FindParent

Prototype        : struct @{"CNetFileEntry" LINK "cnetinclude:files.h/main" 4} *FindParent(struct CNetFileEntry *list);

Purpose          : Find the parent entry for the current list, if existant.

Arguments        : list - the list to examine

Returns          : pointer to the PARENT dir if found
                   returns pointer to the same list passed as list arg if
                   parent not found/non-existant (eg. current list is ROOT)
                   
Known bugs       : none

See also         : 
@ENDNODE

@NODE "FindPhone" "FindPhone"
@TOC "MAIN"

Function         : FindPhone

Prototype        : long FindPhone( short *n, char *phone, short id );

Purpose          : Find the account number of the user to which a
                   phone number belongs.

Arguments        : n     = pointer to the variable to receive the account
                           to which the phone number belongs
                   phone = the phone number being queried
                   id    = an optional account number for phone number
                           verification

Description      : If id is non-zero, this function will perform a
                   verification and return TRUE if the given phone number
                   belongs to the given account (id)

                   if id is zero, this function will perform a search and,
                   if the phone number was found, will fill n with the
                   accountnumber of the user to whom it belongs and
                   subsequently return TRUE.
                   

Returns          : TRUE if the phone nuber was found/verified
                   FALSE if the phone number was not found/verified

Known bugs       : none
@ENDNODE

