@NODE "HNameToUUCP" "HNameToUUCP"
@TOC "MAIN"

Function         : HNameToUUCP

Prototype        : char *HNameToUUCP( char *hname );

Purpose          : look-up @{"UUCP" LINK "cnetinclude:users.h/main" 154}/MailID by handle/real name

Arguments        : hname - the handle or name of the user to look-up.

Returns          : returns the mail ID associated with the given handle or real name.

                   Note some special cases:
                   
                      FEEDBACK, NEWUSER, SYSOP, AREAFIX and POSTMASTER and return "SYSOP"
                      ROOT returns the mail ID of account #1

                   Note that a handle match will override a real name match.

                   A 0 length string ("") is returned if no mail ID is found
                   for the given hname.

Known bugs       : none

See also         : 
