@NODE "LockAccount" "LockAccount"
@TOC "MAIN"

Function         : LockAccount

Prototype        : struct @{"UserData" LINK "cnetinclude:users.h/main" 67} *LockAccount( short acc );

Purpose          : Lock an account so one may examine or alter account
                   attributes.

Arguments        : acc - the account number of the user to be locked.

Returns          : pointer to the UserData of the desired account.

Notes            : the returned pointer is only valid until UnLockAccount
                   is invoked.

                   Each LockAccount() must be followed by an invokation
                   of @{"UnLockAccount()" LINK "UnLockAccount"}

                   Failure to unlock the account or holding an extremely long
                   hold on a user account lock may result in a degradation
                   in efficiency and/or possible deadlocks if LockAccount is
                   called twice in succession on the same account.

                   The best way to deal with this is lock the account, copy or
                   assign the required UserData attribute(s) to another
                   variable or temporary UserData structure and then
                   immediately unlock the account.

See also         : UnLockAccount
@ENDNODE

