@NODE "UltimateFindParts" "UltimateFindParts"
@TOC "MAIN"

Function         : UltimateFindParts

Prototype        : void UltimateFindParts( char *buffer, long min, long max, long *nparts, long *parts );

Purpose          : Find the number of discrete parts in the given range buffer.

Arguments        : buffer - the buffer containing the range to be examined
                   min    - minimum value to apply to the range
                   max    - the max value to apply to the range
                   nparts - a pointer to a long integer which will receive the number
                            of discrete parts existant in the range.
                   parts  - an array of dual longs representing the min and max
                            values for each part. note that parts should be at
                            least 80 bytes in size (10 * 2 * sizeof(LONG))

Limitations      : the number of parts in a range is limited to 10.

Returns          : none

See Also         : 
@ENDNODE

